{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015QYCixto4sV5Q6FSiHkPAi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue clearly. The configmap `es-config` is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. This is the bootstrap setting that is required for a new Elasticsearch 7.x cluster to elect an initial master.\n\nThe fix is:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap\n2. Restart the pods (rolling restart) so they pick up the new config\n3. Wait for the cluster to form and elect a master\n4. Remove the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting from the ConfigMap (it's a bootstrap-only setting)\n5. Do a rolling restart again to verify the cluster stays healthy without the bootstrap setting\n6. I'll update the ConfigMap to include the three master node names, then trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet so the pods reload the configuration. After that, I'll monitor the cluster health through the Elasticsearch API to confirm the nodes have formed a cluster and elected a master.\n\nOnce the cluster is stable, I'll remove the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting from the ConfigMap and perform another rolling restart to ensure everything continues working without the bootstrap configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1821,"cache_read_input_tokens":32753,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1821},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6635382f-f7b7-41cb-ae69-6822f48dcb5d","uuid":"2d1f5910-23d3-4edf-a10b-70faea5b7cb5","request_id":"req_011CcLyFVYRayYGznQDtdUW3"}
