{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AwKM2cZtQ9XbWmr6yaFbTB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n1. **Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which Elasticsearch 7.x requires to bootstrap an initial master election on a brand-new cluster. Without it, all nodes print \"master not discovered yet\" indefinitely.\n\n2. **Fix applied:** Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the ConfigMap, then triggered a rolling restart of the StatefulSet. The cluster formed immediately and elected `es-cluster-2` as master.\n\n3. **Bootstrap setting removed:** Once the cluster was green, the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting was patched out of the ConfigMap (it's a one-time bootstrap hint — leaving it in after formation is a known operational hazard, as it can interfere with master reelection in some recovery scenarios).\n\n4. **Rolling restart verified:** A second rolling restart with the clean config confirmed the cluster re-forms correctly without the bootstrap setting — all 3 nodes rejoined and the cluster returned to **green** (3 nodes, master elected, 6/6 shards active)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":736,"cache_read_input_tokens":45221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":736},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6635382f-f7b7-41cb-ae69-6822f48dcb5d","uuid":"bec20c16-e819-41ba-bd88-a03c639aeab4","request_id":"req_011CcLzYudrdLSzTiKWHMu8i"}
